Figure 8.1

The figure in the book was created from another software package. Standard scatterplot matrices are easy in R (see the worked code for Box 8.1), but it’s tricky do produce in ggplot with marginal boxplots

Figure 8.2

Use ercit

ercit <- read.csv("data/ercit.csv")
ercit.lm <- lm(distance~ eggs+pronotum+legmass, data=ercit)

First version from first principles; something odd about legmass

me<-resid(lm(distance~pronotum+legmass, data=ercit))
me1<-resid(lm(eggs~pronotum+legmass, data=ercit))
ml<-resid(lm(distance~pronotum+eggs, data=ercit))
ml1<-resid(lm(legmass~pronotum+eggs, data=ercit))
mp<-resid(lm(distance~eggs+legmass, data=ercit))
mp1<-resid(lm(pronotum~eggs+legmass, data=ercit))  
df<-data.frame(ercit,me,me1,ml,ml1,mp,mp1)
pr1<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=me1,y=me))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Eggs",y="Distance")
pr2<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=mp1,y=mp))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Pronotum",y=NULL)
pr3<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=ml1,y=ml))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Leg mass",y=NULL)
f8_2<-pr1+pr2+pr3&theme_qk()

Alternative version with lines and CI, not raw data - not used

#don’t need the response variable here, so I remove it with -1
( mod_vars = all.vars( formula(ercit.lm) )[-1] )
[1] "eggs"     "pronotum" "legmass" 
#Using means, not medians for AV
preddat_fun = function(data, allvars, var) {
     sums = summarise_at(data, 
                         vars( one_of(allvars), -one_of(var) ), 
                         mean) 
     cbind( select_at(data, var), sums)
}

head( preddat_fun(ercit, mod_vars, "eggs") )

pred_dats = mod_vars %>%
     set_names() %>%
     map( ~preddat_fun(ercit, mod_vars, .x) )

preds = pred_dats %>%
     map(~augment(ercit.lm, newdata = .x, se_fit = TRUE) ) %>%
     map(~mutate(.x, 
                 lower = .fitted - 2*.se.fit,
                 upper = .fitted + 2*.se.fit,
                 pred = .fitted ) )

xlabs = c("Eggs", 
          "Pronotum",
          "Leg mass" 
          )

pred_plot = function(data, variable, xlab) {
     ggplot(data, aes(x = .data[[variable]], y = pred) ) +
     geom_line(size = 1) +
          geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), alpha = .25) +
 #         geom_rug(sides = "b") +
          theme_qk() +
          labs(x = xlab,
               y = "Distance") +
          ylim(0, 30)
}

pred_plot(preds[[1]], mod_vars[1], xlabs[1])


all_plots = pmap( list(preds, mod_vars, xlabs), pred_plot)
all_plots

Figure 8.4

#Import loyn data file (loyn.csv) & transform relevant variables
loyn <- read.csv("data/loyn.csv")
loyn$logarea <- log10(loyn$area)
loyn$logdist <- log10(loyn$dist)
#Fit linear model
loyn.lm <- lm(abund~ logarea+logdist+graze+alt+yearisol, data=loyn)
me<-resid(lm(abund~ logarea+logdist+graze+alt, data=loyn))  #yearisol
me1<-resid(lm(yearisol~ logarea+logdist+graze+alt, data=loyn))
ml<-resid(lm(abund~ logarea+logdist+alt+yearisol, data=loyn)) #Grazing
ml1<-resid(lm(graze~ logarea+logdist+alt+yearisol, data=loyn))
mp<-resid(lm(abund~ logdist+graze+alt+yearisol, data=loyn))  #logarea
mp1<-resid(lm(logarea~ logdist+graze+alt+yearisol, data=loyn))  
df<-data.frame(loyn,me,me1,ml,ml1,mp,mp1)
pr1<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=me1,y=me))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Year isolated",y="Abundance")
pr2<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=ml1,y=ml))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Grazing",y=NULL)
pr3<-ggplot(data=df,aes(x=mp1,y=mp))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",color=lc)+
  labs(x="Log(area)",y=NULL)
f8_4<-pr1+pr2+pr3&theme_qk()
f8_4

library(effects)

    lattice::trellis.par.set(effectsTheme())
  to customize lattice options for effects plots.

partridge <- read.csv("data/partridge.csv")
head(partridge,10)
partridge$treatment<-factor(partridge$treatment)
partridge.aov1 <- aov(longev~treatment+thorax+treatment*thorax, data=partridge)
partridge.aov2 <- aov(longev~treatment+thorax, contrasts=list(treatment=contr.sum), data=partridge)
adjmeans <- effect("treatment", partridge.aov2, se=TRUE)
adjmeans<-as.data.frame(adjmeans)
p1<-ggplot(partridge.aov2, aes(x = partridge.aov2$fitted.values, y = partridge.aov2$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = "Predicted thorax length", y = "Residuals", 
       )+
  theme_qk()
p1

ml<-c("None","1 preg","8 preg", "1 virg", "8 virg")
p2<-ggplot(data=partridge,aes(x=thorax,y=longev, group=treatment,shape=treatment, color=treatment))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method="lm", se=FALSE)+
  labs(x="Thorax length",y="Longevity")+
  scale_shape_discrete(name=NULL,labels=ml)+
#  scale_linetype_discrete(name=NULL,labels=ml)+
  ylim(0,100)+
  theme_qk()+
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    legend.text=element_text(size=7)
  )+
  scale_colour_uchicago()
p3<-ggplot(adjmeans, aes(x = treatment, y = fit)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = fit-se, ymax = fit+se), width=0) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width=.6, colour="grey40") +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0),limits=c(0,100))+
  scale_x_discrete(labels=ml)+
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Longevity")+ 
  theme_qk()+
    theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(colour = "black", size=7, angle=45, hjust=1),
    )
f8_8<-p1+p2+p3
f8_8
